record.text: シャンプーまでした(イメージ)

ありがとうございます😊
ちわにゃさんちのワンコも可愛い💕💕

休む間を与えられぬ人間がここにいますよ( ◜ᴗ◝)
何か発表される度に名前見てる気がする…気のせいかな…
このだめだった…もう良すぎる新橋√
やったね！

🧵11/11
These anime are chosen to enhance Japanese language skills according to JLPT levels. Each level focuses on vocabulary and grammar difficulty, ensuring gan enjoyable and effective learning experience.

🧵10/11
Ghost in the Shell
Sci-fi anime with N1-level vocabulary and complex expressions, ideal for advanced learners.

Mononoke
Rich in historical and traditional expressions, offering cultural insights and a deeply engaging storyline.

🧵9/11
◾️N1 Level
Jujutsu Kaisen
Action-packed with sorcery terms, ideal for advanced learners tackling complex grammar and vocabulary. (A personal favorite!)

Neon Genesis Evangelion
Abstract themes and deep dialogue, perfect for advanced learners who love analytical challenges.

🧵8/11
ReLIFE
Youthful anime with everyday expressions and N2-level vocabulary, reflecting modern young people’s conversations.

Your Lie in April
Music-themed with emotional depth, blending everyday dialogue and complex expressions.

🧵7/11
◾️N2 Level
Attack on Titan
Challenging military dialogue with N2-level vocabulary, featuring emotional scenes and command-style expressions.

Hanasaku Iroha
Coming-of-age drama with slightly complex dialogues, teaching honorifics and business-related terms.

🧵6/11
Natsume’s Book of Friends
Gentle language and a heartfelt tale of humans and spirits, perfect for listening practice.

Erased
Mystery with N3-level grammar, suited for intermediate learners.

Non Non Biyori
Relaxing countryside setting with daily conversations and Japanese cultural insights.

🧵5/11
My Hero Academia
This anime follows young people aiming to become superheroes, with scenes of daily life and training. It includes vocabulary related to school life and friendship, making it suitable for N4 learners.

This is also one of my favorite anime.

🧵4/11
◾️N3 Level
One Piece
Pirate adventures with casual and everyday expressions, great for listening practice due to diverse character tones.

Naruto
Ninja-themed with simple language and occasional specialized terms, perfect for N3 learners.

🧵3/11
◾️N4 Level

Chibi Maruko-chan
Daily life anime with family and school vocabulary, using N4-level grammar.

Crayon Shin-chan
Humorous and realistic conversations, though some language is colloquial.

Silver Spoon
Agricultural school setting with some specialized but easy-to-follow vocabulary.

🧵2/11
◾️N5 Level
Doraemon
Simple conversations and fun sci-fi, perfect for kids and beginners.

Shirokuma Cafe
Easy everyday conversations with cute characters, great for beginners.

My Neighbor Totoro
Family-friendly with gentle, easy-to-understand language.
イエスのポジションにルシファーが座った邪悪な聖杯探索みたいな内容で、すごく真面目に悪魔崇拝を描いた感じ(何が起きたのか明言されないのがとても良い)なのでこれ見た後だと「実は悪魔の仕業だったんだ」ってホラーが凄い雑に見えます。
この感動を、(新渡戸の)睡眠に捧げます！！

そうだよねえ…
うちもばーちゃんが育ての親みたいなもんだから、みちるちゃんの時の事なんとなくわかる…
すごい不安で泣きそうだった🥺

うん！
子供もマスクできればお見舞いokらしいから行ってくるよ〜(^｡^)
